Package: grive
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: GNU/Linux client for Google Drive
 Grive is a simple and lightweight Google Drive client for GNU/Linux
 written in C++.
 .
 It can synchronize a directory on your hard disk with your Google
 Drive account, downloading or uploading the files that are not in
 sync.

Package: libgrive0
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Library for access the Google Drive API
 Libgrive is a library for accessing the Google Drive API in
 C++. Google Drive is an online storage service provided by Google
 Inc.

